 specifically, this book reports the findings of a research project conducted in Japan that brought teaching practice to bear upon some of the main conflicting theoretical perspectives on how value judgment should be managed in foreign language education. At the heart of this issue lies the management of prejudice, which is a key dynamic in intercultural dialogue that brings many other factors into play.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aIntercultural communicationxStudy and teaching. 0aIntercultural communication. 0aJudgmentxTerminology. 0aLanguage and culture. 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teaching. 0aLanguages, ModernxMutual intelligibility. 0aLanguages, ModernxStudy and teaching. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Communication Studies.2bisacsh  aForeign Language Teaching.  aIntercultural Communication.  aforeign language education.  aintercultural dialogue.1 aHoughton, Stephanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184769726440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847697264423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847697264/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK